message.content:
You are a senior frontend developer doing a PR review. The task was UXDS002b: "Fix selection/active item style. Raycast uses selection color at 10% alpha for active items (subtle highlight), NOT full accent blue. Update list_item.scss: active bg from $color-accent to rgba($color-accent, 0.1). Active title/subtitle/accessory text stays primary color (no white override). Add new token $color-selection-background: rgba($color-accent, 0.1)."

Review the following changes:

1. In src/styles/_tokens.scss, added: `$color-selection-background: rgba(0, 122, 255, 0.1);` before `$color-code-background`.

2. In src/components/list/list_item/list_item.scss, the `&--active` block changed from:
```scss
&--active {
    background-color: $color-accent;

    .list-item__title {
      color: $color-text-on-accent;
    }

    .list-item__subtitle {
      color: $color-text-on-accent-secondary;
    }

    .list-item__icon {
      color: $color-text-on-accent;
    }

    .list-item__accessory {
      color: $color-text-on-accent-secondary;
    }

    .list-item__accessory-text {
      color: $color-text-on-accent-secondary;
    }
  }
```
to:
```scss
&--active {
    background-color: $color-selection-background;
  }
```

The icon default color in `.list-item__icon` is `$color-text-secondary`. In the active state, with the old code the icon was overridden to white. Now it stays at `$color-text-secondary`.

However, note that most list item icons are colorful SVGs (brand icons like Safari, VS Code, Slack, etc.) that don't use `currentColor` — they have hardcoded colors. So the icon color override mainly affected the magnifying glass or other simple icons.

Please review:
- Is the token correctly defined? Should it reference the variable or use the hardcoded rgba?
- Any edge cases or issues with removing the white text override?
- Does the approach match Raycast's actual behavior?
- Are there any other files that should have been updated?

Be thorough and specific.

